title: Embossed Wool, 19th century
medium:
Medium: wool
Technique: glazed and moire plain weave
description: Thin, loosely woven glazed wool with irregular watered pattern, broad double warp. Selvages. In soft pinkish tan. Said to have been made and used by Quakers.
